OL,3,CSark could run out of fresh water if
OL,4,Cpopulation rises
OL,6,FIt is believed that over the next 10
OL,7,Fto 15 years, drought frequency is
OL,8,Flikely to rise from one in five years
OL,9,Fto one in three.
OL,11,FThe issues of how climate change would
OL,12,Faffect the island has also been
OL,13,Fexplored.
OL,15,FBy the year 2100, water extraction
OL,16,Fcould exceed the amount of rain that
OL,17,Ffalls on the island, which is
OL,18,Fcurrently around 825mm each year.
OL,20,FPaul Amorgie runs a hotel in Sark and
OL,21,Fsays drought is already a problem.
